# Interaction Model Parity Fixture
#
# Documents the expected behavior for the three interaction scenarios:
#
# 1. InteractionLLM auto-respond:
#    - Delegate returns ErrNeedsInteraction with questions
#    - Node has interaction: llm
#    - Runtime invokes interaction model (LLM) to auto-respond
#    - LLM provides answers → delegate re-invoked with answers
#    - Run continues without human pause
#
# 2. InteractionLLMOrHuman auto-respond:
#    - Delegate returns ErrNeedsInteraction with questions
#    - Node has interaction: llm_or_human
#    - Runtime invokes interaction model with wrapped schema (needs_human_input flag)
#    - LLM returns needs_human_input=false → delegate re-invoked
#    - Run continues without human pause
#
# 3. InteractionLLMOrHuman escalation:
#    - Same setup as (2)
#    - LLM returns needs_human_input=true → run pauses
#    - Interaction record created with original questions
#    - Status: paused_waiting_human
#    - Resume flow: human provides answers → delegate re-invoked
#
# Key invariants:
# - InteractionHuman always pauses (no LLM involvement)
# - InteractionNone rejects ErrNeedsInteraction with an error
# - SessionID is preserved for delegate re-invocation continuity
# - Questions map is passed through to interaction record unchanged
# - Schema sanitization: question keys with special characters are replaced with underscores
#
# Schema wrapping for llm_or_human:
# - Original schema fields are preserved
# - needs_human_input (boolean) field is appended
# - Wrapped schema name: "{original}_auto_or_pause"
